Ahead of the premiere and theatrical release of Kunle Afolayan’s latest film, ‘Mokalik’, slated for May 29th and May 31st, 2019 respectively, staff of Eko Electricity Distribution Company (EKEDC) Plc, were treated to an exciting moment at the private screening of the movie on May 3rd, as part of the Workers Day celebrations. This followed the first glamorous private press screening of the movie with Canon Central and North Africa, on March 19, 2019. In attendance at the Eko Disco’s showing of ‘Mokalik’ was the Company’s Managing Director Mr Adeoye Fadeyibi, Chief Legal Officer/ Company Secretary Mr. Wola Joseph, General Manager, Corporate Communications, Mr. Godwin Idemudia, and several Directors of the Disco. Mokalik’ tells the story of an 11-year-old boy, Ponmile, from the middle-class suburbs who spends the day as a lowly apprentice at a mechanic workshop in order to view life from the other side of the tracks… When his father arrives to take him home, Ponmile has to make up his mind if he wants to return to school… or take on his apprenticeship full time. A Golden Effects Pictures production, the film stars award-winning singer, Simi, alongside other prominent actors like Femi Adebayo, Charles Okocha, Faithia Williams, Lateef Oladimeji, and comic actors like Wale Akorede (Okunu), Ayo Ogunshina (Papa Lolo) and Dayo Akinpelu (Alabi Yellow). Speaking about his other plans for the movie, Afolayan says he is open to more private screenings before the premiere and cinema release, adding that the next major stop for the film will be at the Cannes Film Festival in France, this month.